Explain what inheritance is.
Inheritance can be defined as the process where one class acquires the methods and fields of another.
With the use of inheritance the information is made manageable in a hierarchical order.
The class which inherits the properties of other is known as derived subclass.
and the class whose properties are inherited is known as superclass.

Explain what polymorphism is.
Polymorphism is the ability of an object to take on many forms. 
The most common use of polymorphism in OOP occurs when a parent class
reference is used to refer to a child class object.
